    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "How long does the scan take?",
        "answer": "Between 20 and 40 minutes, depending on the joint.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is MRI Extremities painful?",
        "answer": "No. You only need to stay still.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before the scan?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless we’re using contrast—then fast 2 hours.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "When will I get my report?",
        "answer": "Standard cases: next morning. Stat reports: 2 hours.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if I’m claustrophobic?",
        "answer": "We offer headphones, mirrors, and mild sedation. Talk to us beforehand.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Will I need an injection (contrast dye) for my extremity MRI?",
        "answer": "This depends on what your doctor is looking for and the specific information needed from your **MRI Extremities** scan. Contrast dye can help highlight certain structures, inflammation, blood flow, or tumors, making them easier to see. If contrast is recommended for your scan, the reason will be explained to you, and you will have the opportunity to ask questions."
      },
      {
        "question": "How much does an MRI scan for extremities cost at Cadabams Diagnostics?",
        "answer": " The cost of an **MRI scan for extremities price** can vary depending on factors such as the specific body part being scanned, whether contrast dye is used, and your insurance coverage. For detailed information on pricing, insurance coverage, or payment options for your **MRI Extremities** at Cadabams Diagnostics, please contact our billing department directly. We are happy to provide you with the necessary information."
      }
